title: Blurr
subTitle: Suspicious about the circumstances surrounding her twin sister's death, a woman with progressive blindness searches for answers that eventually lead her down a dangerous path.

title: Daas Dev
subTitle: Dev is the heir to the throne who is challenged by his beloved Paro in his political backyard. Chandni loves Dev, although she knows that her love is unrequited.

title: U-Turn
subTitle: A journalist investigating traffic offenders on a flyover becomes embroiled in an investigation after being accused of murdering one of the motorcyclists.

title: Kadvi Hawa
subTitle: A blind old man, worried about the survival and well-being of his son, decides to strike a deal with a debt collector to prevent his child from falling into a debt trap.

title: Silence-Can You Hear It?
subTitle: A seasoned narcotics officer is recruited for a special task force. Subsequently, he uncovers shocking truths while investigating a high-profile murder.

title: Kanjoos Makkichoos
subTitle: Jamnaprasad Pandey intends to send his parents on a pilgrimage. However, things take a devastating turn when they disappear during a flood.

title: Gold
subTitle: Tapan Das, a passionate team manager with a penchant for alcohol, embarks a ragtag group of hockey players on an ambitious quest for independent India's first Olympic gold medal.

title: Tejas
subTitle: A brave Indian pilot sets on a mission to rescue a spy from Pakistan who holds confidential information and faces her inner fears from the past.

title: Tumbbad
subTitle: Vinayak Rao, a resident of the village Tumbbad, repeatedly steals the ill-fated wealth of the evil Hastar, until his greed and heinous acts become the reason for his doom.

title: Mr. & Mrs. Mahi
subTitle: Former cricketer Mahendra marries Mahima, a doctor with a passion for cricket. However, upon discovering her exceptional skills, he encourages her to pursue a professional career in the sport.

title: Dunki
subTitle: Four friends from a small village in Punjab set out on a dangerous journey to reach England without the necessary permits and documents.

title: Rashmi Rocket
subTitle: A small-town girl overcomes all societal barriers to become a national-level athlete, but her glory is meaningless when she must undergo a gender test.

title: Sniff
subTitle: Sunny, who lacks the sense of smell, finds his olfactory abilities enhanced after becoming a victim of a laboratory accident, which turns him into a superhero.

title: The Last Color
subTitle: Choti, a young tightrope walker, wishes to pursue her education but struggles to make a living. She soon befriends Noor, a widow who yearns to play Holi but is forced to live a life of abstinence.

title: Iqbal
subTitle: Iqbal, a speech and hearing impaired boy, wishes to play cricket for the Indian team but his impairment overshadows his talent. Thus, he seeks help from a former cricket player to train him.

title: Joggers' Park
subTitle: Jyotin Chatterjee, a former judge, falls for Jenny, a young and independent woman. However, things take a turn when his family scrutinises their relationship.

title: Faraaz
subTitle: Five terrorists take the staff and customers of Holey Artisan cafe in Dhaka hostage. Faraaz and his friends are among the hostages as the police try to de-escalate the situation.

title: Dhadak
subTitle: A world of uncertainties awaits Madhu and Parthavi as their love transcends class divides and blossoms despite the fierce disapproval of their families.

title: Article 15
subTitle: After witnessing rampant caste-based injustice in rural India, a diligent and moral police officer wages war against the system.

title: Dobaaraa
subTitle: A thunderstorm and a television set facilitate a woman to connect with the past and save a young boy's life. However, the turn of events put her present at risk.

title: Kismat Konnection
subTitle: Raj, an out-of-luck architect, and Priya, an out-of-love social activist, find themselves connected in a strange way by destiny.

title: Sharmaji Namkeen
subTitle: After a widower is forced into early retirement, he sets out to find another occupation to overcome his boredom. He meets a widowed boutique owner, and the two start to form a relationship.

title: Mukkabaaz
subTitle: Shravan Singh, an aspiring boxer, finds an enemy in Bhagwan Das Mishra, the head of a boxing federation. Thereafter, things take a turn for the worse after he falls for Bhagwan's niece, Sunaina.
